<header>
  <h1>Different Types of Calculators</h1>
  <p>An overview of various calculators and their uses.</p>
</header>
 
<article>
  <h2>1. Basic Calculators</h2>
  <p>Basic calculators perform simple arithmetic operations like addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. They are ideal for everyday calculations and quick math tasks.</p>
  <p>Common Uses: Budgeting, shopping, and simple math problems.</p>
 
  <h2>2. Scientific Calculators</h2>
  <p>Scientific calculators offer advanced functions, such as trigonometric, logarithmic, and exponential operations. They are designed for higher-level math, including algebra, calculus, and engineering problems.</p>
  <p>Common Uses: Students, engineers, and scientists.</p>
 
  <h2>3. Graphing Calculators</h2>
  <p>Graphing calculators can plot graphs, solve equations, and perform advanced functions. They often have a screen that displays graphs and data visually.</p>
  <p>Common Uses: Higher education, particularly in mathematics and science fields.</p>
 
  <h2>4. Financial Calculators</h2>
  <p>Financial calculators are specialized for tasks like calculating interest, loan payments, and investment growth. They are commonly used in finance and accounting.</p>
  <p>Common Uses: Financial planning, loans, and investment analysis.</p>
 
  <h2>5. Online & Web-Based Calculators</h2>
  <p>Online calculators are available through websites or mobile apps. They range from basic to advanced calculators, offering accessibility from any device with internet access.</p>
  <p>Common Uses: Quick calculations on the go, accessibility for all users.</p>
</article>
 
